Below is a suggested analysis and build‐plan, broken into the three required parts:

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1)  DESCRIPTION OF THE TARGET IMAGE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
• There are two separate sub‐structures:

  A) “Car”‐like Tower (5 blocks total; stacked in 4 levels):
     – Bottom level: Two horizontally oriented orange cylinders side by side.  
     – Above cylinders: One short, flat green rectangular block (horizontal orientation).  
     – Above green block: One red cube.  
     – Topmost level: One blue cube.

  B) Low Ramp (3 blocks total; all on the same level):
     – Center: One blue cube on the ground.  
     – Left side: An orange wedge whose vertical face meets the blue cube on its right side.  
     – Right side: A mirrored orange wedge whose vertical face meets the blue cube on its left side.

• Total blocks used: 8  
  – Tower uses 5  
  – Ramp uses 3  

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2)  SELECTING NEEDED BLOCKS (MATCHING DICTIONARY INDEX)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
From the dictionary image, you need:

1)  Blue cube  (#1)   – used twice (top of tower, center of ramp)  
2)  Red cube   (#2)   – used once (tower)  
3)  Green block (#4)  – short rectangular, horizontal orientation  
4)  Orange cylinder, horizontal (#9) – used twice (tower “wheels”)  
5)  Orange wedge (#14) – left side of ramp  
6)  Orange wedge (#13) – right side of ramp  

So the final index list (with multiplicities) is:  
• #1 × 2  
• #2 × 1  
• #4 × 1  
• #9 × 2  
• #13 × 1  
• #14 × 1  

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3)  STEP‐BY‐STEP ASSEMBLY INSTRUCTIONS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
{
  Step1: Move block with index #9
  Step2: Move block with index #9
  Step3: Move block with index #4
  Step4: Move block with index #2
  Step5: Move block with index #1
  Step6: Move block with index #14
  Step7: Move block with index #1
  Step8: Move block with index #13
}

In this sequence, Steps 1–5 build the “car” tower from the ground up.  
Steps 6–8 place the left ramp wedge, the central blue cube, and the right ramp wedge.
